The paper discusses the construction of pseudorandom sequences for use in communications and remote sensing, which are topics related to information theory (cs.IT) and cryptography (cs.CR). The focus on autocorrelation and crosscorrelation suggests a connection to signal processing (cs.SI) and networked systems (cs.NI). Finally, the use of binary sequences and aperiodic correlation suggests a connection to discrete structures (cs.DS).
